When an transaction takes an account as writable, that account is locked and other transactions that want to access that account (for read or write are queued for later).  A best practice to allow for as many concurrent transactions as possible is to reduce the amount of writable accounts to a minimum and structure the writable accounts so that they’re unlikely to conflict (ie, an account per user instead of a single large account used by all users)
